## 🧱 Step 1: Create State Interface

```java
interface OrderState {
    void next(Order order);
    void cancel(Order order);
    String getStatus();
}
```

---

## 🧱 Step 2: Concrete States

### ▶️ Placed State

```java
class PlacedState implements OrderState {

    @Override
    public void next(Order order) {
        order.setState(new PreparingState());
    }

    @Override
    public void cancel(Order order) {
        order.setState(new CancelledState());
    }

    @Override
    public String getStatus() {
        return "PLACED";
    }
}
```

---

### ▶️ Preparing State

```java
class PreparingState implements OrderState {

    @Override
    public void next(Order order) {
        order.setState(new OutForDeliveryState());
    }

    @Override
    public void cancel(Order order) {
        order.setState(new CancelledState());
    }

    @Override
    public String getStatus() {
        return "PREPARING";
    }
}
```

---

### ▶️ Out For Delivery

```java
class OutForDeliveryState implements OrderState {

    @Override
    public void next(Order order) {
        order.setState(new DeliveredState());
    }

    @Override
    public void cancel(Order order) {
        System.out.println("Cannot cancel now!");
    }

    @Override
    public String getStatus() {
        return "OUT_FOR_DELIVERY";
    }
}
```

---

### ▶️ Delivered State

```java
class DeliveredState implements OrderState {

    @Override
    public void next(Order order) {
        System.out.println("Already Delivered!");
    }

    @Override
    public void cancel(Order order) {
        System.out.println("Cannot cancel after delivery!");
    }

    @Override
    public String getStatus() {
        return "DELIVERED";
    }
}
```

---

### ▶️ Cancelled State

```java
class CancelledState implements OrderState {

    @Override
    public void next(Order order) {
        System.out.println("Order is cancelled!");
    }

    @Override
    public void cancel(Order order) {
        System.out.println("Already cancelled!");
    }

    @Override
    public String getStatus() {
        return "CANCELLED";
    }
}
```

---

## 🧱 Step 3: Context Class (Order)

```java
class Order {
    private OrderState state;

    public Order() {
        this.state = new PlacedState(); // initial state
    }

    public void setState(OrderState state) {
        this.state = state;
    }

    public void next() {
        state.next(this);
    }

    public void cancel() {
        state.cancel(this);
    }

    public void printStatus() {
        System.out.println(state.getStatus());
    }
}
```

---

## 🧪 Usage

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Order order = new Order();

        order.printStatus(); // PLACED
        order.next();

        order.printStatus(); // PREPARING
        order.next();

        order.printStatus(); // OUT_FOR_DELIVERY
        order.next();

        order.printStatus(); // DELIVERED
    }
}
```

---

## 🎯 Key Advantages (Interview Gold 🔥)

### ✅ 1. No if-else

👉 Clean & scalable code

### ✅ 2. Open-Closed Principle Follow

👉 New state = new class (no modification)

### ✅ 3. Single Responsibility

* Order → state hold
* State classes → behavior define

### ✅ 4. Safe Changes

👉 Bug in one state → rest unaffected

---

## 🧠 RATANE KA TARIKA (Memory Trick)

### 💡 1 Line याद रखो:

> **"State alag, behavior alag"**

---

### 🧩 Flow याद करो:

```
1. Interface (State)
2. Multiple State Classes
3. Context (Order)
4. State changes via next()
```

---

### 🧠 Visual Trick:

👉 Imagine:

* Order = Player 🎮
* States = Levels 🎯
* next() = Next Level Button

---

### 🔥 Shortcut Formula:

```
Variable (Order)
    ↓
Holds → State Interface
    ↓
Concrete Classes (Placed, Preparing…)
    ↓
Each class decides → next state
```

---

## ⚠️ Important Edge Case (Interview Twist)

👉 Question:
**What if state transitions are NOT sequential?**

Example:

* Placed → Direct Delivered

👉 Hint:

* Use **Map / Strategy inside State**
* या external **State Transition Manager**

(Advanced topic – interviewer impress करने के लिए बोल सकते हो 😎)

---

## 🧾 Final Summary

| Concept       | Meaning                                |
| ------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| State Pattern | Object behavior changes based on state |
| Core Idea     | Move state logic to separate classes   |
| जब use करें   | Multiple states + transitions          |
| Avoid         | if-else jungle                         |

